Solve the Java challenge with excitement! Here's the code that solves the problem of comparing squares with sums for each pair of integers:
```java
import java.util.Scanner;

public class Main {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
    int n = sc.nextInt(); // number of pairs

    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
      int a = sc.nextInt();
      int b = sc.nextInt();
      int sumSquared = (a + b) * (a + b);
      int squaredSum = a * a + b * b;

      if (sumSquared < squaredSum) {
        System.out.println("<");
      } else if (sumSquared > squaredSum) {
        System.out.println(">");
      } else {
        System.out.println("=");
      }
    }
    sc.close();
  }
}
```
With this Java solution, you'll be thrilled to compare squares and sums for each pair, discovering the relationships between them!

